; 1. Global Attributes (can be used on any HTML element)

1. accesskey – Defines a shortcut key to activate/focus an element

2. class – Specifies one or more class names for an element (used for styling)

3. contenteditable – Indicates whether the element's content is editable

4. data-* – Custom data attributes

5. dir – Specifies the text direction (ltr, rtl, auto)

6. draggable – Specifies whether the element is draggable

7. hidden – Hides the element

8. id – Specifies a unique id for an element

9. lang – Specifies the language of the element's content

10. spellcheck – Specifies whether the element is subject to spell checking

11. style – Inline CSS styles

12. tabindex – Specifies the tab order of an element

13. title – Specifies extra information (tooltip)

14. translate – Specifies whether the content of an element should be translated